DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->add(y=>'Real');

$a = random(-10,-1,1);
$b = random(1,10,1);
$c = random(1,10,1);

$x = random(2,10,1);

$ans= Compute("$c/(2*$x+$a)");


Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Let \(y=x^{2}=$a x+$b\) and \(\frac{dz}{dx}=$c\). Find \(\frac{dz}{dy}\) when \(x=$x\)
$BR
\(\frac{dz}{dx}=\)\{ ans_rule(20) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;


ANS( $ans->cmp());


Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_SOLUTION
${PAR}SOLUTION:${PAR}

We want to find \(\frac{dz}{dy}\). We know \(\frac{dz}{dx}\) and we can compute \(\frac{dy}{dx}\), hence we compute:
$BR
\(\frac{dy}{dx}=2x+$a\), hence at \(x=$x\) we have \(\frac{dy}{dx}=2*$x+$a\)
$BR
\(\frac{dz}{dy}=\frac{dz/dx}{dy/dx}=$ans\)


END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

COMMENT('MathObject version.');

